						<summary>

						<p>Broken slab lying near the Śiva temple.</p>						

						<p>9th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This undated record may be assigned to the 9th century of the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>Incomplete. Seems to refers to death <hi rend="italic">(aṇicheḷa)</hi> of Nivāṟarāḍu the son of certain Kalligōlor Sindarāju and Ugrapottuja.</p>						

